YOU CAN COPY THIS ROUTINES INTO YOU OWN MODULPOOL (IN YOUR NAMESPACE). THEN YOU CAN MODIFY THIS ROUTINES TO YOUR REQUIREMENTS. PLEASE ACTIVY THE ADDITIONAL USAGE OF YOUR MODULPOOL WITH THE BASIS PARAMETER "NAME MODULPOOL FOR USER EXITS" IN THE CUSTOMIZING FOR THE ORGPUBLISHER FOR SAP SOLUTIONS. INPUT PARAMETERS FOR FORM ROUTINE: ---------------------------------- P_IN INPUT VALUE OF INFOTYPE FIELD OR SPECIAL FUNCTION P_PARM STRUCTURE WITH ALL FIELDS OF CURRENCT LEVEL STATEMENT FROM OUTPUT FORMAT (SEE STRUCTURE /EHR/S71_USER_EXIT_PARM IN DATA DICTIONARY). THIS IMPORT STATEMENTS ARE OPTIONAL (SEE ALSO FORM ROUTINE EXAMPLE_IMPORT_MEMORY) CURRENCT INFOTYPE: IMPORT P_INFTY FROM MEMORY ID C_MEMORY_ID_INFTY. VALUES FROM STRUCTURE STRUC FILLED VIA LOGICAL DATABASE PCH: IMPORT G_STRUC FROM MEMORY ID C_MEMORY_ID_STRUC. VALUES FROM STRUCTURE OBJEC FILLED VIA LOGICAL DATABASE PCH: IMPORT G_OBJEC FROM MEMORY ID C_MEMORY_ID_OBJEC. TABLE WITH LANGUAGES USED FOR TEXT FIELDS (FILLED WITH CONTENTS OF T778L OR WITH ONE SELECTED LANGUAGE DEPENDING FROM OPTIONS IN SELECTION SCREEN) IMPORT GT_LANGU FROM MEMORY ID C_MEMORY_ID_LANGU. OUTPUT PARAMETERS: ------------------ P_OUT NEW VALUE FOR OUTPUT FIELD P_PARM-SUBRC RETURN CODE, IF USER EXIT USED IN A IF STATEMENT. 0 --> CONDITION IS TRUE NOT 0 --> CONDITION IS FALSE ----------------------------------------------------------------------- DIESER MODULPOOL ENTHÄLT FORMROUTINEN, DIE IM ORGPUBLISHER FOR SAP SOLUTIONS ALS USEREXITS AUFGERUFEN WERDEN KÖNNEN. NACH KOPIEREN DER ROUTINE IN EINEN EIGENEN MODULPOOL (IN IHREM NAMENSRAUM) KÖNNEN SIE DIESE ROUTINEN AN IHRE ANFORDERUNGEN ANPASSEN. DER AUFRUF DES MODULPOOL IN IHREM NAMENSRAUM MUSS ÜBER DEN BASISPARAMETER "NAME MODULPOOL FÜR USER EXITS" IM CUSTOMIZING VOM ORGPUBLISHER FOR SAP SOLUTIONS AKTIERT WERDEN EINGABEPARAMETER FÜR USER EXIT FORMROUTINEN: -------------------------------------------- P_IN EINGABEWERT VOM INFOTYPFELD ODER DER SPEZIALFUNKTION P_PARM STRUKTUR MIT ALLEN FELDERN DER AKTUELLEN AUSGABEANWEISUNG DES AUSGABEFORMATS (SIHE STRUKTUR /EHR/S71_USER_EXIT_PARM IM DICTIONARY). DIESE ABAP-ANWEISUNGEN KÖNNEN VERWENDET WERDEN, UM WEITERE DATEN ZU BESCHAFFEN (SIEHE AUCH FORMROUTINE EXAMPLE_IMPORT_MEMORY). AKTUELLER INFOTYP: IMPORT P_INFTY FROM MEMORY ID C_MEMORY_ID_INFTY. INHALT DER STRUKTUR STRUC, DIE ÜBER DIE LOGISCHE DATENBANK PCH GEFÜLLT WIRD: IMPORT G_STRUC FROM MEMORY ID C_MEMORY_ID_STRUC. INHALT DER STRUKTUR OBJEC, DIE ÜBER DIE LOGISCHE DATENBANK PCH GEFÜLLT WIRD: IMPORT G_OBJEC FROM MEMORY ID C_MEMORY_ID_OBJEC. TABELLE MIT DEN SPRACHEN, MIT DENEN TEXTDATEN GELESEN WERDEN (GEFÜLLT ENTWEDER AUS TABELLE T778L ODER MIT EINER BESTIMMTEN SPRACHE, ABHÄNGIG VON OPTIONEN IN SELEKTIONSBILDSCHIM). IMPORT GT_LANGU FROM MEMORY ID C_MEMORY_ID_LANGU. OF THIS REPORT PROGRAM IS TO PERFORM THE VARIOUS PLAN CALCULATIONS, COMPARE THEM AND THEN REPORT ALL THE CALCULATIONS AS SMARTFORM OUTPUT. THIS IS THE MAIN REPORT PROGRAM FOR PENSION CALCULATION. THIS CALLS VARIOUS FUNCTION MODULES TO COMPUTE DIFFERENT PLAN CALCULATIONS, COMPARES THE CALCULATED VALUES AND THEN DECIDE FINAL PENSION PAYABLE AMOUNT BASED ON THE SELECTION OPTIONS, ACTUARY MASTER AND VARIOUS PARAMETER TABLES (CUSTOM TABLE). IT MAINLY CALLS THE FOLLOWING FUNCTION MODULES: A. RRB CALCULATIONS B. NSC PLAN CALCULATIONS C. SG PLAN CALCULATIONS D. POST BENEFIT REDUCTIONS E. LUMP SUM CALCULATIONS F. MINIMUM BENEFIT DETERMINATIONS G. SERVICE YEAR DETERMINATIONS ALL THE PLAN CALCULATIONS ARE DISPLAYED AS MULTI-PAGES OF SMARTFORM OUTPUT.

Long Description: PURPOSE: THIS PROGRAM UPDATES PRICES FOR COST CENTER AND ACTIVITY TYPE COMBINATIONS. INITIALLY THE PROGRAM WAS DESIGNED TO CREATE PARALLEL SESSIONS BASED ON THE NUMBER OF AVAILA- -BLE WORK PROCESSES. BUT APPARANTLY THE ACTIVITY ALLOC- -ATION PROGRAM CANNOT BE RUN IN PARALLEL OR IN OTHER WORDS, WE WILL RUN INTO LOCK ISSUES, IF WE TRY TO UPDA- -TE THE DIFFERENT ACTIVITIES FOR THE SAME COST OBJECT (IN OUR CASE COST CENTER). THERE ARE NUMEROUS OSS NOTES EXPLAINING THE LOCKS FOR THE ACTIVITY/COST CENTER COMBO ISSUE 79634, 644364, 940407 TO NAME A FEW. BECAUSE OF THIS WE JUST DIVIDE THE DATA INTO SMALLER PACKETS AND PROCESS IT (TO AVOID MEMORY ISSUES).
IN RFCHKN10, COMPANY CODE IS NOW A SELECT OPTION
